An Act to require an extended producer responsibility agreement as a prerequisite for eligibility
as a certified offshore wind company.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 8A, Chapter 23J, of the General Laws, as so appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after subsection (b) the following words:- “No
3 offshore wind company shall be eligible to be deemed a certified offshore wind company
4 pursuant to subsection (b) without first submitting to the center evidence of an executed producer
5 responsibility agreement, signed under the pains and penalties of perjury by a person expressly
6 authorized to contract on behalf of the offshore wind company.”
